item.dc:creator: @IlikeArrays IlikeArrays
item.description:
@IlikeArrays wrote:

Originally it was

Java/JAGeX Audio+Graphics Extension.

en.wikipedia.org

Jagex

Jagex Limited is a British video game developer and publisher based at the St John's Innovation Centre in Cambridge, England. It is best known for RuneScape and Old School RuneScape, collectively known as the world's largest free-to-play massively multiplayer online role-playing game. The company's name comes from its original slogan, "Java Gaming Experts". In addition to RuneScape, Jagex has released multiple casual games on its FunOrb portal, as well as other titles.
